# AFC-010 — Enterprise Accounts Receivable (AR)

Priority: 20 / 10

Estimated effort: 14–18 weeks
Estimated screens: 260+
Estimated APIs: 900+
Estimated database tables: ~250

## Vision

Every receivable is automatically created, tracked, collected, reconciled and posted to the ledger. The AR platform is the Revenue Collection Engine for the enterprise and a single source of truth for receivables across loans, deposits, gold loans and other products.

## Scope

- Receivable creation (invoices, schedules, EMIs and ad-hoc charges)
- Receipt capture (cash, bank transfers, UPI, cards, cheques, standing instructions)
- Allocation engine (rules-driven, configurable allocation order and partial allocations)
- Collection workflows (dunning, field collections, agency handoffs)
- Promise-to-pay, settlements, waivers and write-offs
- Customer ledger, aging and reconciliation
- Accounting event generation and journal posting
- Reporting, KPIs and analytics (including ML-based scoring)
- Audit trail and compliance controls

## Core Modules

- Invoice & Receivable Engine
- Installment / EMI Scheduler
- Receipt Capture & Posting
- Allocation & Auto-allocation Engine
- Collection Management & Cases
- Promise-to-Pay & Settlement Workflow
- Write-off / Recovery / Legal Case Management
- Customer Ledger & Aging
- Analytics & AI (scoring, prioritization, forecasting)
- Accounting Event Engine (journals, posting, GL integration)

## Integration Matrix

- Loan Management: EMI schedules, principal/interest mapping
- Gold Loan: interest, auction recoveries
- Deposit Management: charges and penalties
- Collections: case and activity sync
- CRM: customer contacts, interactions and notes
- Payment Gateway / Banking: UPI, cards, NEFT/RTGS/IMPS, NACH
- Treasury / Cash & Bank: cash posting and reconciliation
- General Ledger: journal ingestion and chart-of-accounts mapping
- Document Management (DMS): legal notices, agreements
- Notification Engine: SMS/WhatsApp/email reminders

## Events (domain)

- RECEIVABLE_CREATED
- EMI_GENERATED
- RECEIPT_RECEIVED
- RECEIPT_ALLOCATED
- COLLECTION_STARTED
- PROMISE_TO_PAY_CREATED
- SETTLEMENT_APPROVED
- WRITE_OFF_COMPLETED
- RECOVERY_STARTED

